  "prompt": "What advice do you have for a seventeen year old who is pretty confused in life?",
  "response": "Here are some pieces of advice for a confused 17-year-old:\n\n1. Personal Development\n- It's okay to not have everything figured out\n- Focus on self-discovery and exploring your interests\n- Learn about yourself through experiences\n- Be patient with your personal growth\n\n2. Education and Future\n- Keep your options open\n- Don't feel pressured to have a perfect life plan\n- Explore different career paths and subjects\n- Consider internships or part-time jobs to gain experience\n- Stay curious and open to learning\n\n3. Mental Health\n- Talk to trusted adults (parents, teachers, counselors)\n- Practice self-care and manage stress\n- It's normal to feel uncertain\n- Don't compare yourself to others\n- Seek help if you're struggling emotionally\n\n4. Skills and Growth\n- Develop practical skills (communication, financial literacy)\n- Try new activities and hobbies\n- Build self-confidence\n- Learn from mistakes\n- Practice resilience\n\n5. Social Connections\n- Maintain healthy relationships\n- Surround yourself with supportive people\n- Seek positive influences\n- Communicate openly with friends and family\n\n6. Long-term Perspective\n- Remember that life is a journey\n- Setbacks are opportunities for growth\n- Stay adaptable and flexible\n- Believe in your potential\n\nRemember: You're still young, and it's perfectly normal to feel confused.",
